metadata.name: Letter #154
metadata.description:
This is a letter from the computer to you by asemic writing. Imagine what message is written on it.

The artwork is inspired from Shodo(書道) that is known as Japanese calligraphy.
Shodo is the way of writing Kanji and Kana characters with a brush in India ink.
It's one of the traditional Japanese arts.

Paper Color and Ink Color combinations has 18 variations.
Aspect Ratio has 5 variations.
Font Size has 3 variations.
Font Weight has 3 variations.
Font Style has 3 variations.
Each character is randomly generated by a mathematical algorithm.

Controls (in live view):
- Press [f] to switch full screen on and off
- Press [s] to download a PNG file with windowsize
- Press [l] to download a PNG file with large size 4800 pixel  (wait a minutes)

Create with p5.js

metadata.name: a fleeting moment #156
metadata.description:
Abstract expressionism always has been, and always will be, my first love. With this piece, the initial premise was "can I write a bit of code that will render images in the style that I actually paint in real life?" 

It took several full days of poking and prodding, and I departed from the original mission once I had what I was looking for, but in general, I think I succeeded. My wife was looking over my shoulder at one point, and thought I was looking at a scan of one of my actual paintings, which sounds like success to me. 

Created with love in p5.js

metadata.name: glory hole$ #663
metadata.description:
our consciousness as humans can be distilled into a crudely fashioned hole at an abandoned dave & busters and the meditative state that is endured while sitting on a neglected toilet praying for the sound of disrupted waters. glory holes embody anonymity and pleasure for pleasure's sake. they are creations that cannot be destroyed, as they exist in the memories of anyone who uses or witnesses. many speculate that the carving of the hole is the purest form of human ingenuity and the desire to explore the unknown. formerly limited to the physical space. these glory holes transcend space and time. and exist in that same unknown that tempts us all. legalize ground beef. create nothing. consume everything.

HUGE thank you to @PureSpider for the layered PNG template, this dream would not have been realized without you friend.

metadata.name: ABSTRACTION #4
metadata.description:
Re-appropriating Andy Warhol's "Marilyn Monroe, 1967," (originally appropriated from Eugene Kornmann's photo of the actress) as a generative art piece. 

How will we look back upon our Icons? 
Once we pick them apart, can we ever put them back together again?

Technical notes:
There are no image files contained within the package: the script places random shapes by looking up the coordinates and colors in an included text file. A random "Chaos" value is introduced, and then compounded by a growing "Entropy" value. The final result is a completely unique 36" x 36" artwork. Some will be so uniform in pattern that they are instantly recognizable as expressions of the inspirational work. Most will be a gradient of sorts, from order to chaos. A rare few will be completely transformed by disorder.

There are 25 named color palettes for these 32 editions.

Collectors: Select "open live," then once loaded, click on the image to save a printable 36" x 36" version (300ppi)
